Description:
Family Home in Prime Location!
In one of Coburg's best pockets lies this majestic newly built townhouse with style & quality that is sure to impress. With just a short stroll to Sydney Road, Bell Street, Nicholson Street and minutes' walk to Coburg Train Station, Sydney Road tram and Bell Street bus interchange and Upfield Bike Path, this property is surrounded by numerous shops and cafes!
Downstairs features a light filled formal living area with polished Engineered Hardwood floors and reverse cycle Mitsubishi split system. Adjoining onto the light filled open plan kitchen/meals and living area with astonishing features including 900mm Smeg appliances, dishwasher, 40mm Calcutta stone bench tops with a waterfall finish and complemented with Calcutta splash back, under mount sink with pendent lights and an abundance of cupboard space. Walking through the hallway you will notice the separate guest bedroom which is serviced by a modern central designer bathroom with a shower, toilet and a bathtub and internal/external access to the single lock up garage featuring a European laundry and opening out to the path of your own private courtyard.
Upstairs you will find three generous size bedrooms all with built in wardrobes, the master bedroom includes your own private ensuite while the other two bedrooms are complemented with a modern bathroom. Additional features throughout this stunning property include multiple split systems, alarm system and LED downlights.
This property is truly a masterpiece, come and see for yourself!

Description:
Impressive Space with Light and Location
One of only four in a well-maintained block, this two-storey townhouse is a must-see for home buyers and investors alike with its generous dimensions, immaculate presentation and prized location within the Strathmore Secondary College zone. Easy-living excellence, the home's light-filled interior comprises three spacious upstairs bedrooms (two with BIRs, master with WIR), two-way central bathroom as well as separate WCs on each level. Add to this a sizeable front lounge leading through to the open dining area and adjoining kitchen complete with brand-new cooking appliances. Description:
Compelling Californian
Featuring soaring ceilings with handsome details and a position close to everything, this three bedroom Californian Bungalow beckons. On the market for the first time in a quarter of a century, the tightly held home comprises a living room with gas coal fireplace, recently updated kitchen/dining with new gas stove and gas heater, vast, flexible, screened entertaining area and private rear garden. A mirrored BIR features in the main bedroom, the bathroom is conveniently central and further assets include Baltic pine floorboards, leadlight, heating and cooling. Parking is provided by a long side driveway and garage, while the position is close to transport, schools, Harmony Park, local shops and Lincoln Mills Homemaker Centre. Add your own touches and be rewarded for years to come.

Description:
Conveniently close to it all.
This fantastic apartment is ideally located only steps to Batman train station, close to Sydney Rd tram and shops - both in Sydney Rd and also along Gaffney St including Bunnings, Officeworks and Coles. The home has 2 good sized bedrooms with BIR's, a lovely living area with oversized, north facing glass doors which allow natural light to fill the space and direct access to the lovely balcony. The apartment also well serviced by a lovely kitchen with gas cooktop (part of the open plan living area), a central bathroom, separate euro-style laundry, split system air conditioner, secure car park, storage cage and video intercom entrance. Ideal for first home buyers, investors or down sizers. Your inspection will impress.

Description:
SOLD
Located for convenience, this large two bedroom apartment is walking distance to Batman station with Upfield Bike Path at your door. Scaled to impress, the interior is introduced by a vast open living domain with plentiful space for both lounge and dining. Glass doors open to a low maintenance alfresco terrace boasting a sundrenched northerly aspect. Generous indoor/outdoor living spaces are complemented by double bedrooms, oriented to capture city glimpses. The two-tone kitchen, a bright bathroom and European laundry deliver excellent service. There's also split system air conditioning, intercom entry and secure parking. Easy living is sure to attract new buyers, investors and downsizers. Adding appeal is cul-de-sac tranquillity and all within close proximity to Coburg North Village shopping precinct, Coburg North Primary School, Sydney Road shops and caf√©s, Farmer's Market and the Merri Creek bike trail.

Description:
Stunning new custom-designed home in a great position
Crafted for effortless contemporary living in a sought-after inner city pocket, this stunning new residence boasts a state-of-the-art custom design across two levels. It is located steps from city trams and just a short stroll to Moreland station, Sydney Road shops, local cafes and schools including St Fidelis Primary. Filled with natural light at the back is a spacious open plan living and dining area, which leads onto a private sunny courtyard. Dressed in marble benchtops, the stylish kitchen has stainless steel Smeg appliances, Fenix cabinetry and a walk-in pantry. Upstairs is a bright office or retreat, and plush master bedroom with a walk-in robe and ensuite. There is also a second ensuited bedroom plus a good sized downstairs bedroom and sleek marble bathroom. It features a separate laundry, European oak flooring, a Bosch alarm system, video intercom, ducted heating and cooling, data cabling, double glazing, a water tank and a double garage with an automatic roller door and ROW access.
